  "response": "I don't have personal opinions, but I can share that among fans of **\"The Big Bang Theory,\"** some characters receive mixed reactions. For example:\n\n- **Barry Kripke:** Portrayed as a rival to the main characters, Barry often engages in antagonistic behavior and sarcastic remarks, which some viewers find less likable compared to the more endearing main cast.\n  \n- **Leslie Winkle:** While intelligent and competent, Leslie's somewhat abrasive personality and minimal screen time have led some fans to feel she doesn't integrate as seamlessly with the group.\n\n- **Penny's Ex-Boyfriend, Zack:** His character sometimes serves as a foil to highlight Penny's growth, but his portrayal can come across as less developed or relatable.\n\nIt's important to note that perceptions of characters can vary widely among viewers, and what one person might find less appealing, another might enjoy for different reasons.",
